    <article class="mddtpp-article__docs">
      <section id="documentation/basicexample">
        <h4 class="mddtpp-section__title">Basic Example</h4>
        <p class="mddtpp-section__note">
          <strong>Note: </strong>
          Starting from v1.2.0 the all the files have been renamed from md-date-time-picker.* to mdDateTimePicker.* so make sure to update it
        </p>
        <p class="mddtpp-section__note">
          <strong>Note: </strong>
          Starting from v2.0.0 there is only one build
        </p>
        <p class="mddtpp-p">
          Let us begin by creating a very simple dialog. You can specify properties as key value pairs inside an object. As shown below.
        </p>
        <pre>
          <code>
            var dialog = new mdDateTimePicker({
              type: 'date'
            });
          </code>
        </pre>
      </section>
